  "prompt": "What substitutes can be used for Kirby Dry Foam Carpet Shampoo?",
  "response": "If you're looking for substitutes for Kirby Dry Foam Carpet Shampoo, there are several options available:\n\n1. **Rug Doctor Carpet Cleaner**: Offers various formulations, including pet and deep cleaner versions.\n   \n2. **Hoover Carpet Cleaner Solutions**: Known for their effective carpet cleaning solutions suitable for a range of carpet types.\n\n3. **Woolite Carpet and Upholstery Cleaner**: A trusted brand for fabric care.\n\n4. **Bissell Carpet Cleaning Solutions**: Designed to work with Bissell carpet cleaners, these solutions are effective for deep cleaning.\n\n5. **Folex Carpet Spot Remover**: Highly recommended for spot treatments and overall carpet cleaning.\n\n6. **Nature\u2019s Miracle Carpet Shampoo**: Pet-friendly option designed to eliminate stains and odors.\n\n7. **Zep Commercial Carpet Shampoo**: Suitable for larger commercial cleaning needs and home use.\n\n8. **OxiClean Carpet and Area Rug Cleaner**: Known for its powerful stain-removing capabilities.\n\n9. **Simple Green Carpet Cleaner**: Eco-friendly carpet cleaning option.\n\n10. **DIY Solution**: You can create a homemade carpet cleaner using white vinegar, water, and a few drops of essential oils for fragrance. \n\nWhen choosing a substitute, consider the specific needs of your carpet type, any sensitivities or allergies, and the presence of pets or children in the home to ensure the best results.",
